reviewText:
Early Access Review

TLDR:
Jet Racing Extreme is a simple, fast racing game with well-made damaging and destruction system. It is fun for a little bit but it is not anything special and is not worth its price. I feel like developers wanted to make a good arcade game but then mixed it with realistic damage and destruction system and it didn't match well.

Details:

+ Fast-paced gameplay with nice (but somehow weird) steering. The speed one can reach here is really high and it is exciting;
+ Destruction and damage system - it is very good, detailed thing in this game. You can damage your wheels and even get them completely destroyed and you would still be able to drive your car. That is an interesting and well-made idea;
+ Maps are nice and interesting;

+/- Car upgrades - There are many upgrades available to your vehicle parts which is nice. Although, I somehow had enough money to upgrade everything to its max level after my very first race and I did not even know why. That completely ruined the upgrade system for me. Hopefully they will change it someday in the future;

- Sometimes you could get a feeling that the game is actually too fast - it is very nice to feel the speed but your vehicle always crash after touching literally anything. That is frustrating and I would rather like to enjoy the speed rather than seeing my car crashing so often in such an arcade game;
- I feel like developer mistakenly mixed 2 different, opposite things in this game - they created realistic game if it comes to damage, destructions and physics but I did not like that - I feel like this game should be a very fast-paced arcade racer in which you could get unbelievable, enormous speeds and enjoy the fast ride without worrying about your car getting crashed that much. Unfortunately, that is impossible - your car gets destroyed everytime it touches something and it frustrates a lot - it completely removes the arcade" thing;
- Music is repetetive and boring. So are sound effects - honestly they were making me annoyed and I could not stand them after a while;
- In-game purchases - the game itself is a port from mobile game but I try not to judge it by that. However

recommended:
 single player mode is boring - you do not even compete with any other AI-controlled cars. You just drive alone;
- Graphics could be better;

Summing up:
I cannot recommend Jet Racing Extreme at its current state. It is not worth the price with what it offers at the moment. It has very good damage and destruction system and physics are nice. However
